###cluster related commands###

1.kubectl api-resources | more                                          ##shows api resources like endponits(ep),ns
2.kubectl cluster-info                                                  ##Show cluster info
3.kubectl config current-context                                        ##Show current context
4.kubectl config get-contexts                                           ##List all contexts
5.kubectl config use-context <name>                                     ##Switch context
6.kubectl create deployment my-nginx --image=nginx --dry-run=client -o yml >deployment.yml  ##create deployment yml 
7.kubectl diff -f new-deployment.yml | more                             ##difference between current running deployment and new deployment
8.kubectl delete -f deployment.yml                                      ##delete deployment
9.
